<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador to Zimbabwe Holds National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 1 (xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to Zimbabwe
Liu Guijin held a reception here this afternoon to celebrate the
48th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China.
</P>
<P>
In his speech to some 300 Tanzanians and foreign diplomats
attending the reception, Liu Guijin said two major historic
events took place in China this year and these have brought
special significance to the National Day celebrations this time.
</P>
<P>
On July 1st, China resumed exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong after the region had been under British rule for over 150
years, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
And last month, the Communist Party of China successfully
convened its 15th congress, which laid down guidelines for China
to enter the 21st century by holding high the great banner of
Deng Xiaoping theory for building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the guests on the achievements after China
adopted reform and opening policies in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
In a toast, Zimbabwe's Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs
Nicholas Goche conveyed to the Chinese government and people
congratulations and best wishes from the Zimbabwean government
and people.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his government's satisfaction with the existing
friendship and cooperation between the two countries and peoples.
</P>
<P>
Goche said he hoped the two sides would explore other avenues
to further promote bilateral technical cooperation and trade.
</P>
<P>
The reception attracted more than 300 government officials,
foreign diplomats and Zimbabwean friends from various walks of
life, as well as Chinese working and living in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
