<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E. African Countries to Develop Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The East African
Cooperation (EAC) is planning to develop and modernize road
infrastructure linking Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania, a news
dispatch from Arusha in northern Tanzania said today.
</P>
<P>
The project was endorsed at the eighth meeting of the EAC
commission, the highest decision-making body which met in August
in Arusha, EAC officials were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank, the European Union and the African Development
Bank have been approached for financial assistance to the
project.
</P>
<P>
A task force of road experts met in Arusha on Tuesday under
the auspices of the EAC to review the project and prepare
document for a donors' meeting on the multi-million shillings
project.
</P>
<P>
EAC officials are of the view that the road network will
facilitate the smooth flow of goods, persons and services and
speed up the region's political, economic and social integration.
</P>
</TEXT>
