<HEADLINE> No Asian Players in Quarterfinals at China Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Leander Paes of India was
defeated by third seed Thomas Johansson of Sweden 5-7, 1-6 here on
Wednesday in the China Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Paes, last year's Olympic bronze medalist, played a spirited
match against Johansson who is ranked 34th in the world. But the
Swedish player took the control of the game with his strong serves
and base-line play to win the match.
</P>
<P>
Johansson and Kenneth Carlsen of Denmark, Gianluca Pozzi of
Italy, Magnus Gustafsson of Sweden, and Byron Black of Zimbabwe
all advanced into the quarterfinals after Wedensday's matches.
</P>
<P>
Carlsen beat Micael Tillstrom of Sweden 6-2, 6-0 while
Gustafsson beat qualifier David Rikl of the Czech Republic 6-2,
6-4 after being down 0-2 in the first set and 0-3 in the second
set.
</P>
<P>
Pozzi scored a straight set win over South African Grant
Stafford. Byron Black had the toughest match of the day,
overcoming Justin Gimmelstob of the United States 3-6, 7-5, 6-4.
</P>
</TEXT>
