<HEADLINE> People across China Celebrate National Day (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 1 (Xinhua) -- People of all ethnic groups
across China today celebrated the 48th founding anniversary of the
People's Republic with flag-raising ceremonies and a variety of
festivities.
</P>
<P>
Some 260,000 people gathered at Tiananmen Square in Beijing to
see the daily flag-raising ceremony held at the crack of
dawn. Deafening applause burst from the crowd when the Five-Star
Red Flag reached the top of the mast within about two minutes.
</P>
<P>
Liu Kuiji, a wartime hero in his 70s, said this was the fifth
time since 1950 that he has watched the solemn National Day
ceremony on the square.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very excited. This National Day came right after the 15th
National Party Congress, which has opened a new chapter for the
history of the motherland," the revolutionary veteran said.
</P>
<P>
Ma Fengliang, a young man of Hui ethnic group, one of China's
ethnic minorities, came to the capital from the remote
northwestern Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
"The national flag makes all of us in the square that our
hearts are connected," he said. "And I can feel more acutely the
warmth of the big family of our motherland."
</P>
<P>
A young man from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR), founded on July 1 this year, said that watching the
flag-raising on the first National Day since Hong Kong's return to
its motherland would be the most cherished memory of his life.
</P>
</TEXT>
