<HEADLINE> People across China Celebrate National Day (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Early this morning, more than 3,000 people in the HKSAR,
including major local officials and noted figures, attended the
region's first official National Day flag-raising ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The event was held in front of the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center Extension, the venue for the Sino-British Hong
Kong handover ceremony at midnight on June 30.
</P>
<P>
Similar activities were held today in many other cities across
the country, including Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian
Province, Hangzhou, Ningbo and Wenzhou cities in Zhejiang Province
and Zhenjiang in Jiangsu Province. Each ceremony drew thousands of
participants.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a jubilant atmosphere permeated all major cities
throughout China, especially capitals of various provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities, which were decorated with
fresh flowers, colorful banners and bright lights.
</P>
<P>
In Changsha, capital of central-south China's Hunan Province,
more than 1,000 pots of flowers lined the city's major streets,
while thousands of banners and balloons fluttered and floated in
the wind.
</P>
<P>
In Haikou, capital of China's southernmost island province
Hainan, coconut trees along the streets looked more attractive at
night than in daytime, glowing in the emerald floodlights
installed for the occasion.
</P>
<P>
In the 80,000-square-meter downtown square of Chengdu, capital
of southwest China's Sichuan Province, tens of thousands of local
residents enjoyed the party atmosphere and had pictures taken on
the large lawn.
</P>
