Theory and rally closely around the CPC Central Committee with
Party General Secretary Jiang Zemin at its core.
</P>
<P>
Lu Yihua, general manager of a shareholding company in
Shijiazhuang, capital of the north China province of Hebei, said
that "the congress's report confirmed that the shareholding system
is an effective way to realize the public ownership. This has
greatly inspired our staff members who have decided to seize the
opportunity to turn our company into a bigger one."
</P>
<P>
Lu was a delegate to the recent 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
In the northwestern province of Shanxi, government officials
visited factories and villages to express their solicitude for
workers and farmers. In the northern Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region, officials and ordinary people thoroughly reviewed the
report.
</P>
<P>
While many Chinese people have four days holiday at National
Day, some Chinese are at work.
</P>
<P>
At the Anshan Iron and Steel Corporation, workers are busy in
front of the blast furnaces. An ironworks turned out 22,763 tons
of iron on September 30, 1,263 tons more than scheduled, and on
National Day it turned out a record 23,500 tons of pig iron.
</P>
<P>
Jia Qinglin, mayor of Beijing, went to Tiananmen Square, bus
stations and a vegetable market to express his care and concern
for the police, bus drivers and conductors, and vendors. Ranking
officials of other provinces and cities have also done the same.
 
