<BODY>
<HEADLINE> STD's Victims in S. Leone Top 5,000: Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, October 1 (Xinhua) -- An estimated 5,000 woman in
Sierra Leone, aged between 14 and 29 years are victims of
sexually transmitted diseases (STD) in several identified sample
areas including the capital Freetown.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Health officials here in an interview
with Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, Dombali and TonkoliL in the
north, Kumena in the east and the Western Area which includes the
capital, recorded the highest cases of STD in the last seven
years, one official said.
</P>
<P>
Public Health Officer Festus Kamarakei described the
statistics as alarming. He said, "everything must be done to save
young girls from this disease." 
</P>
