in Sierra Leone six days which expired Tuesday to either register
or re-register or stop publication.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the 1980 Newspapers Act, which journalists have
consistently urged the authorities to repeal, Turay said,
"registration and re-registration of newspapers are not intended
to stifle the press."
</P>
<P>
"The Act protects the public from liberal and seditious
newspaper reporting. Some guidelines must be put in place to
ensure responsible journalism," he added.
</P>
<P>
Six out of the current 13 were put on sale Wednesday. 
