<HEADLINE> Transportation Facilities for Three Gorges Project Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The 302-meter-long and
21-meter-wide Tanjiatuo Bridge spanning a temporary shiplock at
the Three Gorges Dam has become operational.
</P>
<P>
Its opening to traffic concluded the construction of a group of
transportation facilities, including a 28-kilometer-long highway
for special use that connects the Yichang-Huangshi expressway, two
main bridges, namely the Tanjiatuo Bridge and Yangtze Bridge at
Xiling and one leading port, which link the dam area with Yichang
City, the headquarter of the Three Gorges project.
</P>
<P>
The highway, which was opened to traffic one year ago, involved
34 bridges and five culverts alone. It cuts the traffic time from
the dam area to the city of Yichang from an hour and a half to 20
minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Yangjiawan Port with six 1,000-ton berths, which was also
built last year, will serve as a transfer station for materials
for construction of the project.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimated that a total of 40 million tons of
construction materials need to be transported via highways and
waterways before the whole dam project is scheduled to be finished
in 2009.  
</P>
</TEXT>
