<HEADLINE> Australia, Thailand Sign Legal Cooperation Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Australian Attorney-General
Daryl Williams and visiting Thai Justice Minister Suwit Khunkitti
today signed a judicial cooperation treaty covering civil and
commercial matters.
</P>
<P>
"This bilateral treaty was an initiative of the Thai government
and represents the first of its kind between Australia and other
nations in the Asia-Pacific region," Williams said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"The agreement will significantly facilitate the service of
process and the taking of evidence in civil and commercial legal
proceedings involving Australia and Thailand, allowing direct
access to designated authorities in both countries without the
need to resort to the diplomatic channels."
</P>
<P>
Australians and Thais will now be able to access each other's
courts, legal aid and any reductions or exemptions from the costs
of proceedings.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also encourages the use of arbitration to settle
commercial disputes.  
