<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Locking of Yangtze Important to Three Gorges Dam Construction (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Locking of the main stream of
the Yangtze River is vital to the successful construction of the
gigantic water control project at the Three Gorges.
</P>
<P>
The locking is scheduled to take place from November 6-8,
signaling the end of the first-phase construction of the dam and
the beginning of the second.
</P>
<P>
The entire water control project will be constructed in three
phases over a 17-year period.
</P>
<P>
During the first stage from 1993 to 1997, preparatory work,
mainly resettlement of residents in the area to be submerged,
should be completed.
</P>
<P>
The second stage will start when the Yangtze is cut off by two
parallel earth-and-stone cofferdams this November, and extend
through the year 2003.
</P>
<P>
During the third stage from 2004 to 2009, the 630,000-sq-m
riverbed between the two cofferdams will be drained to make way
for dam construction and the generator stations to be installed on
the northern bank of the river.
</P>
<P>
Work on the auxiliary facilities began in 1993, and they have
been basically completed. Building of a temporary ship lock and
lift has been finished on schedule, while construction of the
cofferdams from both banks of the river has proceeded swiftly.
</P>
<P>
Locking of the Yangtze is a vital prerequisite for bringing the
Three Gorges Dam into a profitable period. The Three Gorges Dam
involves a static investment of 90.05 billion yuan (10.85 billion
US dollars) and raise needed funding has been difficult, therefore
income from power generation will be one of major sources of
financing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971002.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Locking of Yangtze Important to Three Gorges Dam Construction (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Twenty-six generators will be installed at the Three Gorges
Project; the first two will start power generation in the year
2003. And by the year 2009, the water control dam will have
generated 293 billion kw/hours of electricity and will have
directly accumulated some 80 billion yuan (9.6 billion US dollars)
in funding for continuous construction of the dam.
</P>
<P>
Power generation at the Three Gorges Dam is guaranteed as the
Yangtze River Three Gorges Project Development Corporation has
signed contracts with two European-led conglomerates to provide 14
generators, each with a generating capacity of 700,000
kw. Contractors for building of other necessary facilities have
also been hired.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, locking of the Yangtze will also serve as the testing
ground for all technology used in the dam construction.  
</P>
