</P>
<P>
About 80 Chinese companies are presenting at the trade fair
more than 400 traditional and newly-developed products, ranging
from machinery, electronics, electric appliances to textiles,
garments, arts and crafts.
</P>
<P>
More hi-tech products, like advanced electronic appliances,
computers and precision instruments, were seen on display this
year.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also features the participation of a great
number of well-known Chinese companies.
</P>
<P>
Well-known brands, such as Panda, Haier, Hisense and Konka
(electronics) and Qingqi (motorcycles), covered almost half of
the exhibition floor space.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition, sponsored by China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade and China Chamber of
International Trade, covered an exhibition area of 2,000 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
Vice Chairman of China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade, Cui Yushan, Deputy Director of China Center
for South Africa Studies, Lin Lin and South Africa's Gauteng
Premier Tokyo Sexwale, Mayor of Greater Johannesburg Isaac Mogase
and Chairman of South African Chamber of Business Hugo Snyckers,
were present at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is China's largest trading partner in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries has witnessed rapid growth in
recent years. Statistics show that bilateral trade in 1995
reached 1.32 billion U.S. Dollars, from only tens of millions of
Dollars in 1991. 
</P>
