<HEADLINE> S. Africa Promoting Economic Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa attaches
great importance to existing economic and trade relations between
China and South Africa, and expressed hope to further promote the
relations, a South African official said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the China Trade Expo '97,
Premier Tokyo Sexwale of the Gauteng Provincial government said
that China, as a rising economic giant of the world, would be
very helpful to South Africa's economic development.
</P>
<P>
"The sheer size of China provides our own business people with
enormous business opportunities not only as a huge market and an
investment destination, but more crucially as providing the
crucial foothold to enter the bustling southeast Asian economic
hinterland.
</P>
<P>
"We thus see this China Expo '97 as part of a broader strategy
to consolidate China-South Africa relations, as an opportunity
for increased trade between our two countries, as providing our
prospective business people and government officials with the
opportunity to get to know one another," Sexwale said.
</P>
<P>
China and South Africa, which are expecting to establish full
diplomatic relations before the end of the year, have been making
efforts to promote bilateral trade in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Sexwale said that China had invested over 40 million U.S.
Dollars in a chrome mine operation in the Northern Province. The
volume of trade between South Africa and China now stands at well
over 2.7 billion U.S. Dollars and is growing day by day, he said.
</P>
<P>
The premier pointed out that the full diplomatic relations
between the two countries would create the requisite legal
framework for "reciprocal intergovernmental exchanges". A
cooperation agreement between the two countries would soon be
concluded, he said.
</P>
<P>
Isaac Mogase, the mayor of Greater Johannesburg, also
participated in the opening ceremony of the China Trade Expo '97,
the fifth of its kind in South Africa since 1993.
</P>
<P>
He said the exposition was presenting "a good opportunity of
trade and exchanges for people in the business circles of the two
countries".
</P>
<P>
Mogase expressed belief that there is great potential and vast
prospects for economic and trade cooperation between South Africa
and China.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the exposition, about 80 Chinese companies
have presented more than 400 traditional and newly-developed
products ranging from machinery, electronics, electric
applicances to textiles and garments, arts and crafts. 
</P>
