<HEADLINE> Palestinian Council Member Explains Reason for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 2 (Xinhua)-- Palestinian Council (PC)
member Haider Abdul Shafi said today that improper cooperation
between PC and the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) is the
main reason for his resignation.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference today at the PC administrative
office in Ramallah, West Bank, Shafi said the PNA has never taken
into consideration the PC's recommendations on human rights issue.
</P>
<P>
Shafi, who submitted his resignation Wednesday, said his
resignation is irreversible.
</P>
<P>
The PC has attempted to respond to citizen's complaints and
tried to transcend its responsibility in defending citizen's
rights, but the PNA placed obstacles for the PC in this matter,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Explaining other reasons for his resignation, Shafi said the
PNA has recently shut down 17 Hamas (Islamic Resistance Movement)
institutions in Gaza Strip and the West Bank, which provide
humanitarian services to the citizens, but it didn't clarify the
reason for closing those institutions.
</P>
<P>
He said there were many complaints by citizens to the PC on the
security apparatus' violations, but the PNA did not discuss the
PC's recommendations on this matter.
</P>
<P>
Shafi's resignation will be discussed in the PC's next session
two weeks later.
</P>
<P>
Shafi, a physician from the Gaza city, established the
Democratic Building Movement prior to the PC election in 1996,
and ran under that name. 
</P>
