<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Builds More Jewish Settlements in West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Israel has built 3,183
settlements in the West Bank and another 4,714 are being built,
according to a report by the Peace Now, a joint
Palestinian-Israeli peace movement, which is available here today.
</P>
<P>
Israel's intention of building more settlements is to help
provide Israel with a crucial military footing in the West Bank
because each settlement requires military protection, political
observers here noted.
</P>
<P>
The Peace Now which has sent out 17 groups this summer to scour
the new Jewish settlements in the West Bank found that under the
Israeli government led by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu,
large-scale construction of Jewish settlements took place close to
the pre-1967 border along the Green Line between Tel Aviv and
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Aharon Domb, Secretary General of the Council of Jewish
Settlements in the West Bank and Gaza Strip, puts the number of
homes now being built at 6,500, 2,000 of which are deep inside
the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, hundreds of housing units are under
construction at Givat Ze'ev, a suburb north of
Jerusalem. Meanwhile, Jewish housing construction is under way at
Nahliel, north of Ramallah, a community of 60 Jewish families
surrounded by Palestinian villages.
</P>
<P>
In Eli and Shilo between Ramallah and Nablus, finished homes on
the mountain ridge road which are banned from sale under the
former Labor government are now on the market. Israel promised to
build more when they were sold.
</P>
<P>
In Afrat near Gosh Etzion, south of Bethlehem, 300 new housing
units will be built, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Besides huge investments on housing constructions, the
Netanyahu's government this year also allocated around 84.3
million U.S. dollars on construction of roads, lighting, sewerage,
factories and hotels within the settlement areas in the West bank,
according to the Peace Now.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said that the Netanyahu government has not only
reversed the policy of Labor government's cutting of financial
incentive to Jewish settlers, but also unlocked 3,000 housing
units in the West Bank that the Labor government had frozen.
</P>
<P>
They noted that Israel's settlement policy has become a big
obstacle to the Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiations, harming
the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971002.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Residents Move Out of Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- By mid-September, most of the
39,600 residents had been moved out of areas in central China's
Hubei Province, which will be submerged in early November when
locking begins on the Three Gorges Dam on the the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The Bureau of Resettlement and Development of the Three Gorges
Project Construction Committee of the State Council, made the
announcement in late September.
</P>
<P>
A reservoir with a storing capacity of 39.3 billion cu m and a
projected water height of 175 m will be built at the gigantic dam,
which will be completed in four phases over 17 years.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the water level of the Yangtze at the Three Gorges
area is recorded at 78 m. It will be driven to the first-stage
height of 82.24 m after the main stream of the Yangtze is cut off
from November 6-8.
</P>
<P>
The four-meter rise in water level will cause the inundation of
part of seven counties of central China's Hubei Province and and
southwest China's Chongqing Municipality, which required 39,600
local residents to move out of their homes before June 1996, when
flood season of the Yangtze begins.
</P>
<P>
By mid-September, residential quarters with a combined floor
space of some 700,000 sq m had been built to accommodate residents
from the soon-to-be submerged areas. Some 86 of the 116 factories
have also moved from the areas, with the remaining ones pledging
to leave before next May.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Dam will prevent flooding on the Yangtze and
will have an annual power output of 84.7 billion kwh. The entire
project will be completed in 17 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
