<HEADLINE> Trust and Investment Company Taps Overseas Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hainan International Trust
and Investment Company in southernmost China has made new headway
in tapping overseas capital market, with its successfully offering
of 14 billion Japanese yen in bonds in Japan.
</P>
<P>
All the funds pooled from the bond issue will be directed into
the major construction projects in the island province, according
to company officials.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1988 as a provincial government-funded
investment company, the Hainan International Trust and Investment
Company became one of the ten financial organs that were
authorized to raise capital from overseas in 1989.
</P>
<P>
The company has since actively tapped the overseas capital
market, establishing relationships with more than 100 banks
overseas.
</P>
<P>
It channeled its first overseas loans of 15 million US dollars
into Hainan in late 1992, and has since then raised funds through
issuing bonds in Hong Kong, Japan, and Singapore. In 1996, the
company provided a total of 1.18 billion yuan (142 million US
dollars) for the construction of key projects in Hainan province.
</P>
<P>
</P>
