<HEADLINE> Internet Saves Chinese Boy's Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 2 (Xinhua) -- A one-year-old Chinese boy
suffering from congenital heart disease got helps from the United
States after his father sent a message on the Internet calling for
help, according to a "China Daily" report today.
</P>
<P>
The boy returned to east China's Shanghai municipality last
week after receiving a successful operation provided by a hospital
at New Jersey, the U.S., the report said.
</P>
<P>
The baby was born with serious heart problems early this
year. But many local hospitals were unable to cure the disease for
technological reasons.
</P>
<P>
The boy's father then sent a message on the Internet calling
for help. He later received response from a US woman named Gloria,
who managed to find the hospital that agreed to conduct an
operation for the boy free of charge.
</P>
<P>
One of Gloria's sons once suffered from the same heart disease
and recuperated following an operation. 
</P>
