<DOCNO> XIE19971002.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Mainland's Tariffs Cut Benefits Macao: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The cut of tariffs from Wednesday
on some 5,000 kinds of commodities by the Chinese interior customs
authorities will benefit Macao, local traders and economic experts
said.
</P>
<P>
The tariff cut may help increase shipments of some goods from
Hong Kong to the Chinese interior areas via Macao, although it has no
immediate effect, some local ocean-shipping dealers said.
</P>
<P>
They said that Hong Kong will benefit the most from the tariff
cut because it is the biggest entrepot between the Chinese
interior areas and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese interior customs authorities cut tariffs on
imported goods from an average 23 percent to 17 percent from
October 1. Those goods are mainly farm produce and high-tech
goods.
</P>
<P>
The reduction of tariffs is also beneficial to Macao in the
long run, said Liu Chak Wan, a top executive of the Macao
Association of Importers and Exporters.
</P>
<P>
"Although the current amount of goods Macao re-exports to the
Chinese interior is small, Macao can become a bonded warehouse for
some low-tariffed goods destined for the Chinese interior," he
told the Macao Daily News. "Part of the goods can be stored or
processed in Macao and re-exported to the Chinese interior later."
</P>
<P>
Macao businessmen may also benefit from the lowered tariffs
when they establish plants in the Chinese interior, said Chui Sai
Cheong, president of the Macao Association of Economics Study.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, many Macao manufacturers have shifted
their plants to the Pearl River Delta and other interior areas.
Such trend continues as a result of increasingly higher cost of
production in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Macao businessmen, who are doing business in the Chinese
interior, will be able to buy cheaper imported equipment and raw
materials to expand their production there, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
