<HEADLINE> France Offers to Help Algeria Find Political Solution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 2 (Xinhua) -- France today offered to help find
a political solution to the six-year-old conflict in Algeria but
attached a condition that all parties there should join the
process.
</P>
<P>
"All the organizations, all the countries which are deeply
saddened by what is going on (in Algeria) cannot but express their
readiness" to join the initiative, said French Foreign Minister
Hubert Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
"All the parties, if they want it and if they ask for it," the
top French diplomat told Radio-Television Luxembourg (RTL), should
have a part in the political solution.
</P>
<P>
As regard to the proposed French role in the fresh offer,
Vedrine said it is not "based on the feeling of interference but
on humanity, friendship and solidarity."
</P>
<P>
"Algeria is there. We are there. We should think about the
future, build close relations after all these tragedies," he said.
</P>
<P>
He repeated French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin's recent
criticism against the Algerian government for resorting to
force in trying to put down the Muslim insurrection.
</P>
<P>
"There is an extreme violence (in Algeria) and it is true that
the state, which ... is brought to fight an extremely violent
terrorism, employs the force of the state," said Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
The French foreign minister also appealed to Algerians to hold
the forthcoming local elections under "the most possibly
incontestable condition." 
</P>
</TEXT>
