<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops High-Speed Bogie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, October 2 (Xinhua) -- A high-speed bogie, or
undercarriage, for passenger trains has been developed in
Changchun, which has passed the test at a speed of 300 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
Changchun Passenger Train Plant, which developed the equipment,
is also the largest producer of passenger trains in China.
</P>
<P>
The bogie has passed early trial tests on an experimental track
at Southwest China Communications University, located in the
northeast province of Jilin.
</P>
<P>
Wang Huanzhang, chief engineer of the plant, said that the
successful development of the high-speed bogie will pave the way
for China to produce faster trains.
</P>
<P>
It is possible that the bogie be widely used on China-made
passenger trains running at a speeds of 200 to 300 km per hour, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the plant will continue to improve the performance
of the bogie, so as to allow train speed of up to 400 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
