<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Rupiah Falls to Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's rupiah plunged again
Wednesday to record low as the stock exchange bore the brunt of
the worsening currency crisis, dealers and brokers said today.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah slumped to a new low of 3,470 against the U.S.
dollar in the morning session before recovering to 3,370/3,400 at
close against 3,270/90 on opening.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the rupiah's drop to the rise of the dollar
overnight rates in the local market, the sharp fall of other
regional currencies and the high demand for the American dollar.
</P>
<P>
Overnight rates for the American dollar increased to 20 percent
Wednesday from less than 10 percent previously.
</P>
<P>
The rise of overnight rates will surely attract more people to
buy the dollar, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, almost all Southeast Asian currencies plunged to
their new lows Wednesday amid scenes not witnessed since the Thai
baht's shocking flotation in early July.
</P>
<P>
According to analysts, the currency upheaval is entering its
second phase.
</P>
<P>
Bank Indonesia (central bank) Governor Soedradjad Djiwandono
said Wednesday night that the rupiah's fall this week was largely
due to the increase in the demand for American dollars from local
companies.
</P>
<P>
He said many companies bought dollars to pay their
dollar-denominated debts.
</P>
<P>
According to data from business consulting firm the Castle
Group, Indonesian private offshore debt reached 55.52 billion U.S.
dollars last year, of which about 34.24 billion dollars would
mature in less than a year.
</P>
<P>
Stock trading bore the brunt of the worsening currency crisis,
with the composite index, the main price barometer at the Jakarta
Stock Exchange, losing 1.77 percent to close at 536.99 points
after a slight increase the previous day.
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts said the market would remain bearish in the
short-term due to continued uncertainty in the currency market and
the weakening rupiah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
