(D-8) countries will be held in Dhaka in November next year.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's State Minister for Foreign Affairs Abul Hasan
Chowdhury disclosed this at a seminar here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh, Indonesia, Malaysia, Nigeria, Pakistan, Egypt, Iran
and Turkey have set up the D-8 group for greater economic
cooperation among them.
</P>
<P>
The member countries had recently decided that the first summit
be held in Dhaka, the state minister said.
</P>
<P>
Before the summit, preparatory meetings will be held at
different levels, he added.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state and government of the eight countries had
decided while forming the D-8 Group in Istanbul on May 12-13 this
year that the experts from each of the eight countries would form
working groups for sectors in which they have experience and
achieved success.
</P>
<P>
The working groups will share the experience and expertise of
the member countries in the relevant sectors for overall
socio-economic development of the eight countries. 
