Ministry's Business Economics Department.
</P>
<P>
Thai exports to Nigeria grew 95 percent to 2.84 billion baht
(81 million dollars), giving Thailand a trade surplus of 2.62
billion baht (74.8 million dollars), double that for the same
period of last year, the department was quoted today by local
press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has had a trade surplus with Nigeria for five
consecutive years. Rice made up 85 percent of Thailand's sales to
Nigeria.  
