<DOCNO> XIE19971002.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Bans Import of Ostriches From U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of
Agriculture of Brazil has decided to ban the import of ostriches
and ornament birds from United States after the discovery of virus
carried by imported ostriches.
</P>
<P>
The decision came out after several ostriches carrying
Newscastle virus, which causes bird pneumoencephatilis, entered
the country through the Rio Airport, the Ministry of Agriculture
secretary Enio Marquez was quoted as saying by the local press
today.
</P>
<P>
A batch of Ostriches imported from the U.S. were already dead
before their arrival in Brazil on June 15, Marques said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture examined the birds and isolated the
virus, the official said.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the discovery, the Ministry of Agriculture called
on other countries to follow the example of Brazil in banning the
import of ostriches from the U.S. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
