<HEADLINE> Brazil to Appoint Police Attaches to Diplomatic Missions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government
will appoint Federal Police attaches to its embassies in
Argentina, Paraguay and Colombia, in an effort to facilitate the
exchange of information on crime investigation.
</P>
<P>
Brazil chose Argentina and Paraguay for crime investigation
because of their common partnership in the Southern Common Market
(Mercosur) while it picked Colombia because the frontier they
share is a main corridor for drug and weapons trafficking,
according to the local press today.
</P>
<P>
In another development, U.S. Federal Bureau of Investigation
(FBI) is looking forward to install a representation office in
Brasilia, where its agents will work as "observers," Brazilian
Police director Vicente Helotti was quoted by the press as
saying. 
</P>
