<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 300 Mln Dlrs for Highway Project in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 300
million U.S. dollar loan to Brazil to help its highway improvement
program.
</P>
<P>
The main component of the project is the rehabilitation of some
6,800 kilometers of paved roads. The project, the total cost of
which is estimated at 750 million dollars, is designed to reduce
transportation and road maintenance costs throughout the country,
improving international competitiveness and integration with the
countries of Mercosur, the southern South American common market.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank is providing some 300 million dollars in
co-financing. Local counterpart funds total 150 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, the IDB already approved a 115 million
dollar loan to the state of Ceara and 150 million dollars to the
state of Rio Grande do Sul for highway improvements in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
